---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../../components/nav/SiteHeader.astro';
import { boundaries, gateSemantics } from '../../data/boundaries';
import { STUDIES_URL } from '../../consts';

const title = 'Capability boundaries — DeepCausality CFD';
const description =
  'Where this toolbox stops working, stated where you will hit it, with the measurements behind each limit. Includes four hypotheses the project refuted by running them.';

const refuted = boundaries.filter((b) => b.refuted);
const limits = boundaries.filter((b) => !b.refuted);
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/boundaries/">
  <SiteHeader slot="header" />

  <article class="page bpage">
    <header class="bhead">
      <p class="eyebrow">Capability boundaries</p>
      <h1>Where it stops working.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Every limit below was measured, not estimated. Each says where you hit
        it rather than which feature is missing, because the useful question is
        whether your problem crosses the line.
      </p>
      <p class="lede">
        Four of these refuted something the project believed. Those are first,
        because a toolbox that publishes its disproofs is easier to evaluate
        than one that publishes only results.
      </p>

      <div class="callout callout-warn">
        <p class="callout-title">A passing gate is not a passing physics target</p>
        <p>{gateSemantics}</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="bsection">
      <h2 class="bsection-head">
        <span class="status status-partial">Refuted</span>
        Hypotheses overturned by measurement
      </h2>

      {refuted.map((b) => (
        <section class="bcard panel corner-brackets" id={b.id}>
          <h3>{b.title}</h3>
          <p class="hit"><span class="k">You hit this when</span> {b.hitWhen}</p>

          {b.question && (
            <div class="qa">
              <p class="k">The question asked</p>
              <p class="qtext">{b.question}</p>
            </div>
          )}

          <p class="finding">{b.finding}</p>

          <ul class="nums">
            {b.numbers.map((n) => <li class="num">{n}</li>)}
          </ul>

          {b.attribution && (
            <div class="block">
              <p class="k">Attributed to</p>
              <p>{b.attribution}</p>
            </div>
          )}

          {b.ruledOut && (
            <div class="block block-ruled">
              <p class="k">Ruled out by the measurement</p>
              <ul class="ruled">
                {b.ruledOut.map((r) => <li>{r}</li>)}
              </ul>
            </div>
          )}

          {b.consequence && (
            <div class="block block-consequence">
              <p class="k">What this means for your code</p>
              <p>{b.consequence}</p>
            </div>
          )}

          {b.history && (
            <details class="history">
              <summary>Earlier attempt, and why it was superseded</summary>
              <p>{b.history}</p>
            </details>
          )}

          <p class="src"><code>studies/{b.study}</code></p>
        </section>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="bsection">
      <h2 class="bsection-head">
        <span class="status status-roadmap">Standing</span>
        Limits of the current design
      </h2>

      {limits.map((b) => (
        <section class="bcard panel corner-brackets" id={b.id}>
          <h3>{b.title}</h3>
          <p class="hit"><span class="k">You hit this when</span> {b.hitWhen}</p>
          <p class="finding">{b.finding}</p>
          <ul class="nums">
            {b.numbers.map((n) => <li class="num">{n}</li>)}
          </ul>
          <p class="src"><code>studies/{b.study}</code></p>
        </section>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="bsection">
      <h2 class="bsection-head">What this adds up to</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The compression thesis holds, and its condition is expensive.
          Alignment drives rank, not sharpness. Holding alignment while marching
          needs re-pinning <em>and</em> an exact Rankine–Hugoniot interface, and
          the 3-D fitted marcher that makes the whole approach work is itself
          over its wall-clock budget at the smallest grid measured. The shipped
          corridor runs a 2-D layer for exactly that reason.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every rank measurement uses scalar Burgers with explicit Euler and
          central differences rather than compressible Euler or Navier–Stokes,
          and every one is stated as a lower bound on a live solver's rank. That
          caveat is repeated in each study and is repeated here.
        </p>
        <p>
          Turbulence is staged work, not an exclusion. The validated
          incompressible cases sit at Re 100–1600, and the wake is reported
          rather than gated.
        </p>
        <p>
          Source for every measurement:
          <a href={STUDIES_URL}>deep_causality_cfd/studies/ <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .bpage { max-width: var(--w-panel); }
  .bhead { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .bhead h1 { margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4); }
  .bhead .lede { color: var(--fg-1); max-width: var(--measure); margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .callout p { color: var(--fg-1); font-size: var(--t-body-sm); margin: 0; }

  .bsection { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .bsection-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: baseline;
    font-size: var(--t-h3);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-1);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .bcard {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    scroll-margin-top: calc(var(--header-h) + var(--space-4));
  }
  .bcard h3 { font-size: var(--t-h4); margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); }
  .k {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--t-eyebrow);
    letter-spacing: var(--ls-eyebrow);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-2);
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
  }
  .hit { color: var(--fg-0); font-size: var(--t-body-sm); margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); max-width: var(--measure); }
  .finding { color: var(--fg-1); font-size: var(--t-body-sm); margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); max-width: var(--measure); }

  .nums { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); padding: 0; display: grid; gap: var(--space-2); }
  .nums li {
    color: var(--fg-1);
    padding-left: var(--space-3);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--line-2);
    font-size: var(--t-mono-sm);
  }
  .src { margin: 0; padding-top: var(--space-3); border-top: 1px solid var(--line-1); }
  .src code { font-size: var(--t-eyebrow); color: var(--fg-2); background: none; padding: 0; }

  /* --- Worked negative result --- */

  .qa { margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .qtext {
    color: var(--fg-1);
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--line-2);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .block { margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .block p:last-child {
    color: var(--fg-1);
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  /* Ruled-out causes get the affirmative colour on purpose: eliminating a
     candidate is a positive result, and it is what separates a measured limit
     from an unexplained one. */
  .block-ruled { padding: var(--space-4); background: var(--bg-2); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .ruled { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); }
  .ruled li {
    color: var(--fg-1);
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    position: relative;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .ruled li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 10px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--ok);
  }

  .block-consequence {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-1);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .history {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-1);
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .history summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
    color: var(--fg-1);
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .history summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .history summary::before {
    content: '▸';
    color: var(--fg-2);
    transition: transform var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .history[open] summary::before { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  .history summary:hover { color: var(--fg-0); }
  .history p {
    color: var(--fg-1);
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 0;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
</style>
